4 (q) Not later than sixty (60) days before approving
5 the issuance or extension of a mineral lease for oil, gas,
6 coal or other mineral production on state lands or state
7 school lands under this article, the board of land
8 commissioners shall provide notice of the proposed mineral
9 lease in writing to the board of county commissioners of
10 the county or counties where the state lands or state
11 school lands are to be leased. The board of land
12 commissioners shall provide the board of county
13 commissioners an opportunity to submit or provide public
14 comment on the proposed lease in writing or at the meeting
15 where the lease is to be discussed or approved.
